properties.Name: MarketingProgram
properties.Description:
An administrative vehicle that details the pricing, administration and sales strategy of selling products and services to a Market or Market Segment of consumers.

Ex:
- Low Income Education Loan Program
- Senior Citizenship Program
- Student Shopped Program
- FNMA Community Home Buyers Program
- FNMA Employer-Assisted Housing
- First Time Buyer
- a product specific promotion program
- a program to educate the public or consumers about a product or service
- a support program such as 'product maintenance'

Note:
A Program may also be associated with an Order in which case it identifies the specific Program under which the associated Order was placed or fulfilled.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramName
Columns.Description: The name of the Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramStartDate
Columns.Description: The start date of the Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramEndDate
Columns.Description: The end date of the Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramEligibilityStatement
Columns.Description: A statement that describes the eligibility to participate in the Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramRestrictionStatement
Columns.Description: A statement of the restrictions that apply to access to or participation in the Marketing Program.

Columns.Name: MarketingProgramTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Marketing Program Type.

Columns.Name: SponsoringPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.
